cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD

This paper is about task-oriented dialog systems and text classification, which are both sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. 

The paper also involves machine learning models and evaluation metrics, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The dataset and evaluation also touch on information retrieval (IR) and search, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR. 

Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of handling out-of-scope queries, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
